<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><channel><title>Facebook on EricLog</title><link>https://eric.swiftzer.net/tags/facebook/</link><description>Recent content in Facebook on EricLog</description><generator>Hugo -- 0.141.0</generator><language>zh-tw</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 14 Dec 2012 13:11:57 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://eric.swiftzer.net/tags/facebook/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Facebook for Android 出了更新了！</title><link>https://eric.swiftzer.net/2012/12/facebook-for-android-updated/</link><pubDate>Fri, 14 Dec 2012 13:11:57 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://eric.swiftzer.net/2012/12/facebook-for-android-updated/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="http://chinese.engadget.com/2012/09/12/zuckerberg-html-5-facebook-mobile-app-mistake/">早前&lt;/a> Facebook 創辦人暨現任 CEO Mark Zuckerberg 於訪談中說到以 HTML5 編寫 &lt;a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.facebook.katana">Facebook Android app&lt;/a> 是公司決策上最大的錯誤，今日他們終於不再用 WebView + PHP 顯示貼文了！速度的確快了不少。不過郤引來&lt;a href="http://unwire.hk/2012/12/14/android-facebook-no-more-broken-chinese/software/">一眾香港用戶投訴&lt;/a>，指界面會轉用簡體中文，甚至連&lt;a href="http://hk.apple.nextmedia.com/realtime/finance/20121214/51184200">《蘋果日報》&lt;/a>都有報道，指 Facebook app 出現簡體中文是要打中內地市場。&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>